post_cb({"16490491": {"ParentId": "16490478", "CommentCount": "0", "Body": "<p>It jumps immediately out of the containing <code>while</code> loop (\u00a76.6.1):</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p id=\"so_16490478_16490491_0\">The <code>break</code> statement shall occur only in an <em>iteration-statement</em> or a switch statement and causes termination of the smallest enclosing <em>iteration-statement</em> or switch statement; control passes to the statement following the terminated statement, if any.</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>Consider <a href=\"http://ideone.com/sEM7C4\" rel=\"nofollow\">the following example</a>:</p>\n<pre><code>while (true) {\n    break;\n    std::cout &lt;&lt; \"Never gets here\" &lt;&lt; std::endl;\n}\nstd::cout &lt;&lt; \"Jumps straight to here\" &lt;&lt; std::endl;\n</code></pre>\n", "OwnerUserId": "150634", "PostTypeId": "2", "Id": "16490491", "Score": "4", "CreationDate": "2013-05-10T20:40:33.853", "LastActivityDate": "2013-05-10T20:40:33.853"}, "16490478": {"CommentCount": "5", "ViewCount": "86", "ClosedDate": "2013-05-10T21:11:39.733", "CreationDate": "2013-05-10T20:39:57.477", "LastActivityDate": "2013-05-10T20:42:00.827", "Title": "how works \"break\" within a while-loop in C++?", "PostTypeId": "1", "Id": "16490478", "Score": "-8", "Body": "<p>I have a simple Question: when there's a \"break\"-command within a while-loop, does the program finish the lines until the end of the while-loop and then breaks its repetition or does it jump to the first line after the while-loop when executing the \"break\" - command?</p>\n", "Tags": "<c++>", "OwnerUserId": "1773218", "AnswerCount": "2"}, "16490515": {"ParentId": "16490478", "CommentCount": "0", "Body": "<p>it does the following thing</p>\n<p>The break statement terminates the execution of the nearest enclosing do, for, switch, or while statement in which it appears. Control passes to the statement that follows the terminated statement.</p>\n", "OwnerUserId": "1629397", "PostTypeId": "2", "Id": "16490515", "Score": "1", "CreationDate": "2013-05-10T20:42:00.827", "LastActivityDate": "2013-05-10T20:42:00.827"}, "bq_ids": {"n4140": {"so_16490478_16490491_0": {"section_id": 3910, "quality": 0.95, "length": 19}}, "n3337": {"so_16490478_16490491_0": {"section_id": 3770, "quality": 0.95, "length": 19}}, "n4659": {"so_16490478_16490491_0": {"section_id": 4796, "quality": 0.95, "length": 19}}}});